# Files excluded from the Vercel deployment upload.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: without it the CLI uploaded the whole working directory
# — 293 MB, almost all of it reels/_frames (2.8 GB of rendered video frames).
# Vercel answered the oversized upload with an HTML error page, which the CLI
# tried to parse as JSON and reported as:
#   Error: Unexpected token '<', "<html><h"... is not valid JSON
#
# EVERY PATTERN HERE IS ANCHORED WITH A LEADING SLASH, ON PURPOSE.
# These are gitignore-style patterns, which match at EVERY depth unless
# anchored. An unanchored "supabase/" excluded lib/supabase/ as well as the
# root supabase/ directory, and broke the build with:
#   Module not found: Can't resolve '@/lib/supabase/client'
# The leading slash restricts each rule to the repository root. Do not remove
# it, and anchor anything new you add here.
#
# Only exclude what the BUILD does not need. The build runs on Vercel, so app/,
# components/, lib/, content/ (MDX), public/ and the config files must all stay.

# Local video/reel generation workspace — nothing imports it
/reels/

# Brand and design source files (shipped assets live in public/)
/brand/
/design/

# One-off and maintenance scripts, not part of the build
/scripts/

# Docs and planning notes. Root-level markdown only: the content loaders
# (lib/atlas.ts, lib/blog.ts, lib/academy.ts …) all accept .md as well as .mdx,
# so an unanchored "*.md" would silently drop content from production.
/docs/
/*.md

# Database migrations are applied through Supabase, not at build time.
# Anchored so it cannot match lib/supabase/, which the app imports.
/supabase/

# Local build and tooling artefacts
/.next/
/node_modules/
/.git/
*.tsbuildinfo
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
